album.title: Born to Die - The Paradise Edition

wiki.content:
"Bel Air" is a song by American recording artist Lana Del Rey. It appears on her third extended play, Paradise. Featuring clips from the "Summertime Sadness" music video, a promotional video for "Bel Air" was released to YouTube in early November. The video received much critical acclaim. After the release of Paradise, the song charted in the United Kingdom and France.
 
 Canada.com reviewer Leah Collins called "Bel Air" an Enya-channeled, eerie waltz.
 Conversely, The Huffington Post called both "Bel Air" and "Yayo" Paradise's filler-tracks.
 Dissatisfied with other songs on Paradise, Digital Spy said, on "Bel Air", Del Rey finally gets it right, calling the song "a snowy, Tim Burton-inspired ballad.
